The Vice President gave a speech at the 12th National Hispanic Prayer Breakfast in Washington, D.C. He thanked the faith leaders for their work and expressed gratitude for their ministries. He also brought greetings from President Trump and discussed the recent historic summit with North Korea, emphasizing the commitment to denuclearization and the repatriation of American POWs and MIAs. The Vice President discussed the administration's efforts to strengthen the economy, create jobs, and cut taxes. He highlighted the administration's pro-life stance and commitment to protecting religious freedom. He also addressed the issue of immigration, expressing disappointment in the lack of bipartisan cooperation and urging Democrats to work towards a solution. The Vice President discussed the administration's stance on Cuba, Nicaragua, and Venezuela, emphasizing the need for freedom and democracy in those countries. He concluded by expressing faith in the American people and gratitude for the faith leaders' work.